     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="13"/>
   <head>To the fauourable Le<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ctor
health.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">T</seg>Here were some pages which I thought not
meet to leaue emptie, good Lector, either
for thy sake, or for <hi>Tabaccoes</hi> sake, or
for mine owne sake: for thy sake, because
I wearie not to talke with thee: for <hi>Ta<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>baccoes</hi>
sake, because the worth of it de<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>serueth
some verses: for mine owne sake,
because I neuer hauing sleeped in <hi>Parnassus,</hi> but beeing a
valley Poete, I persuade my selfe that my verse, shall be read
more for the merites of the maetter, then for the value of the
Work<gap reason="illegible" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>man. Therefore I addresse my selfe first to gaze against
a craig, from whence some musicall influence may bed<gap reason="illegible" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>w
my braine.</p>
   <closer>Vt sic repente Poeta prodeam.</closer>
